IMPLEMENTATION MODE — ALWAYS use **generated_class**.

There is no longer a template fallback. Every strategy — even a one-indicator
"EMA 9/21 cross" — must be implemented as a fresh `GeneratedStrategy` Python
class. Set `implementation_mode = "generated_class"`. The list of available
templates above is for indicator-vocabulary inspiration only; do NOT pick one.
Set `template = "custom_generated"`.

Why this rule is non-negotiable: a template runs hard-coded logic and exposes
hard-coded params. If your spec includes a filter or knob the template doesn't
read, that filter silently does nothing — the user sees their RSI filter "in
effect" but the engine ignored it. Generating code every time is the only way
the parameter list, indicators, and entry/exit logic stay in lockstep.

PARAMETER SCHEMA — the `parameters` dict must EXACTLY match
`GeneratedStrategy.default_params`. Same keys, same order. No phantom keys
("adx_threshold" on a strategy with no ADX), no missing keys.

