DATE RANGES

Accept relative phrasing like "past 6 months", "last 2 weeks", "last year",
or absolute dates like "from 2025-06-01 to 2026-01-31". Convert to:

  "date_range": {
     "type": "relative" | "absolute" | "all",
     "value": <int or null>,            // for relative
     "unit":  "day"|"week"|"month"|"year"|null,
     "from":  "<YYYY-MM-DD or null>",   // for absolute
     "to":    "<YYYY-MM-DD or null>"
  }

If the user EXPLICITLY says "all data", "everything", "full history" or similar,
use {"type": "all"}.

If the user says NOTHING about time AND `prior_spec` doesn't already have a
date_range, you MUST set:

  "needs_clarification": true,
  and add to "questions":
      "How far back should I run the backtest? (e.g. last 6 months, last 2 years,
       or all available history)"

Use {"type": "all"} as a placeholder in `date_range` while clarification is
pending — the run won't start until the user answers.

Once the user answers (next turn — `prior_spec` will include their previous
draft, conversation_context will include their reply), drop the question and
fill `date_range` from their answer.

